<!-- S4 Complexity -->
<section class="section" id="s4">
<div class="section-num">Section 04</div>
<h2>QFT Complexity: Counting Gates</h2>
<p>With the circuit structure derived, gate counting is straightforward.</p>
<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">H gates:</div><div class="mstep-body">Exactly n &mdash; one per qubit.</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Ctrl-phase gates:</div><div class="mstep-body">0+1+2+&hellip;+(n&minus;1) = n(n&minus;1)/2</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">SWAP gates (opt.):</div><div class="mstep-body">&lfloor;n/2&rfloor; to reverse output register.</div></div>
  <hr class="math-sep">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--green);">QFT total:</div><div class="mstep-body" style="color:var(--green);font-weight:600;">n(n+1)/2 &asymp; n&sup2;/2 = O(n&sup2;) = O((log&#x2082;N)&sup2;)</div></div>
</div>
<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--red);">Classical FFT:</div><div class="mstep-body" style="color:var(--red);">O(N log N) = O(n&middot;2&#x207F;) &mdash; exponential in n</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--green);">Quantum QFT:</div><div class="mstep-body" style="color:var(--green);">O(n&sup2;) gates &mdash; exponentially fewer!</div></div>
  <hr class="math-sep">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">n=10:</div><div class="mstep-body">Classical: 10,240 ops. Quantum: 55 gates. Ratio: ~186&times;.</div></div>
</div>
<canvas id="cvComplexity" width="540" height="200"></canvas>
<div class="canvas-caption">QFT (n&sup2;, blue) stays flat while classical FFT (n&middot;2&#x207F;, red) explodes exponentially.</div>
