<div style="background:var(--red);color:white;padding:0.45rem 1rem;margin:2rem 0 0;border-radius:var(--border-r);font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.68rem;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;">Part II &mdash; Shor&rsquo;s Algorithm</div>

<!-- S5 Shor Factoring -->
<section class="section" id="s5">
<div class="section-num">Section 05</div>
<h2>Shor&rsquo;s Algorithm: The Factoring Problem</h2>
<p>Shor&rsquo;s algorithm (1994) is the reason quantum computers threaten modern cryptography. It factors a large composite integer n in polynomial time, breaking RSA encryption.</p>
<div class="def">
  <div class="def-title">The Factoring Problem</div>
  <strong>Input:</strong> Composite n (e.g. n=15=3&times;5)<br>
  <strong>Output:</strong> Non-trivial factors<br>
  <strong>Classical:</strong> Try all primes below &radic;n &mdash; exponential in bit-length b = log&#x2082;(n).
</div>
<div class="note-box"><strong>Why is this hard classically?</strong> RSA uses n=p&middot;q with 512-bit primes p, q. Naive approach needs ~2&#x2075;&#xB9;&#xB2; trials. More than atoms in the universe.</div>
<h3>Reduction to order finding</h3>
<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--accent);">Step 1</div><div class="mstep-body">Pick random x with 1 &lt; x &lt; n. Compute gcd(x,n). If gcd &gt; 1: <strong>stop, x is a factor (lucky!)</strong>.</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--accent);">Step 2</div><div class="mstep-body"><strong>Order finding</strong> (the quantum step): find smallest r such that x&#x02B3; mod n = 1.</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--accent);">Step 3</div><div class="mstep-body">If r is odd, or (x&#x02B3;&#xB9;&#xB2;+1) mod n = 0, go back to Step 1 with new x.</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--green);">Step 4</div><div class="mstep-body">gcd(x&#x02B3;&#xB9;&#xB2;&minus;1, n) and gcd(x&#x02B3;&#xB9;&#xB2;+1, n) are non-trivial factors of n!</div></div>
</div>
<h3>Worked example: n = 15</h3>
<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Pick x=2:</div><div class="mstep-body">gcd(2,15)=1 &rarr; proceed.</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Order:</div><div class="mstep-body">2&sup1;=2, 2&sup2;=4, 2&sup3;=8, <strong>2&#x2074; mod 15 = 1</strong> &rarr; r=4 (even &#x2713;)</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Check:</div><div class="mstep-body">(2&sup2;+1) mod 15 = 5 &ne; 0 &#x2713;</div></div>
  <hr class="math-sep">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--green);">Factors:</div><div class="mstep-body">gcd(3,15) = <strong style="color:var(--green);">3</strong> &#x2713; &nbsp;&nbsp; gcd(5,15) = <strong style="color:var(--green);">5</strong> &#x2713;</div></div>
</div>
<div style="border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:6px;padding:1rem;margin:1rem 0;background:#fdfcf8;">
  <div style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:0.6rem;">Interactive: Order Finder</div>
  <div class="controls" style="flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
    <span class="ans-label">n =</span><input id="shor_n" type="number" class="answer-input" value="15" style="width:70px;">
    <span class="ans-label">x =</span><input id="shor_x" type="number" class="answer-input" value="7" style="width:70px;">
    <button class="btn sm" onclick="computeOrder()">Find order</button>
  </div>
  <div class="live" id="orderResult">Enter n and x, then click Find order.</div>
</div>
<div class="ex-block">
  <div class="ex-header"><span class="ex-tag">Ex 5.1</span><span class="ex-title">Order of 7 mod 15</span></div>
  <div class="ex-body"><p>Find smallest r such that 7&#x02B3; mod 15 = 1.</p></div>
  <div class="answer-area">
    <div class="answer-row">
      <span class="ans-label">r =</span>
      <input class="answer-input" id="a51" placeholder="integer" style="width:80px;">
      <button class="btn sm" onclick="chkApprox('a51',4,0,'f51')">Check</button>
      <button class="hint-toggle" onclick="showHint('h51')">hint</button>
    </div>
    <div class="feedback hint" id="h51">7&sup1;=7, 7&sup2;=4 mod 15, 7&sup3;=13 mod 15, 7&#x2074;=1 mod 15. So r=4.</div>
    <div class="feedback" id="f51"></div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- S6 Order Finding Proof -->
<section class="section" id="s6">
<div class="section-num">Section 06</div>
<h2>Why Does Order Finding Give Factors?</h2>
<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Start:</div><div class="mstep-body">x&#x02B3; mod n = 1 &rArr; x&#x02B3;&minus;1 = qn (divisible by n).</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">If r even:</div><div class="mstep-body">x&#x02B3;&minus;1 = (x&#x02B3;&#xB9;&#xB2;+1)(x&#x02B3;&#xB9;&#xB2;&minus;1) = qn</div></div>
  <hr class="math-sep">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--red);">Question:</div><div class="mstep-body">Where are the factors of n in (x&#x02B3;&#xB9;&#xB2;+1)(x&#x02B3;&#xB9;&#xB2;&minus;1)?</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Case 1:</div><div class="mstep-body">n cannot be all in (x&#x02B3;&#xB9;&#xB2;&minus;1): that would mean x&#x02B3;&#xB9;&#xB2; mod n = 1, contradicting minimality of r.</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Case 2:</div><div class="mstep-body">n cannot be all in (x&#x02B3;&#xB9;&#xB2;+1): excluded by Step 3.</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--green);">Conclusion:</div><div class="mstep-body">Factors of n split between the two terms. gcd(x&#x02B3;&#xB9;&#xB2;&plusmn;1, n) gives non-trivial factors. &#x220E;</div></div>
</div>
<div class="insight"><strong>Classical bottleneck is Step 2.</strong> Finding order classically: try r=1,2,&hellip; Expected trials &asymp; n/2 = 2&#x1D47;&#x207B;&#xB9; &mdash; exponential. RSA-1024: ~2&#x2081;&#x2030;&#x2030;&#x2030; trials. The quantum speedup lives entirely here.</div>
<div class="ex-block">
  <div class="ex-header"><span class="ex-tag">Ex 6.1</span><span class="ex-title">Factors from order</span></div>
  <div class="ex-body"><p>n=15, x=7, r=4. Compute gcd(7&sup2;&minus;1,15) and gcd(7&sup2;+1,15).</p></div>
  <div class="answer-area">
    <div class="answer-row">
      <span class="ans-label">gcd(48,15)=</span><input class="answer-input" id="a61a" placeholder="?" style="width:55px;">
      <span class="ans-label">gcd(50,15)=</span><input class="answer-input" id="a61b" placeholder="?" style="width:55px;">
      <button class="btn sm" onclick="chk2('a61a','3','a61b','5','f61')">Check</button>
      <button class="hint-toggle" onclick="showHint('h61')">hint</button>
    </div>
    <div class="feedback hint" id="h61">48=3&times;15+3 &rarr; gcd=3. &nbsp; 50=3&times;15+5 &rarr; gcd=5.</div>
    <div class="feedback" id="f61"></div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- S7 Period Finding -->
<section class="section" id="s7">
<div class="section-num">Section 07</div>
<h2>Period Finding: Linking Shor to QFT</h2>
<p>Order finding is secretly period finding. Define f(&ell;) = x&#x1D4C;&#x2E31; mod n. Then f(&ell;+r) = f(&ell;), so f has period r. Key FFT property: a signal with period P has DFT peaks at multiples of N/P.</p>
<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Exact (N mod P=0):</div><div class="mstep-body">Peaks exactly at m = 0, N/P, 2N/P, &hellip;, (P&minus;1)N/P</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Approximate:</div><div class="mstep-body">Peaks near m &asymp; &ell;&middot;N/P for various &ell;</div></div>
</div>
<canvas id="cvPeriod" width="540" height="220"></canvas>
<div class="canvas-caption">Periodic signal (top) and QFT spectrum (bottom). Peaks reveal the period P.</div>
<div class="controls" style="flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem;">
  <span class="ans-label">Period P:</span>
  <input type="range" id="slP" min="1" max="8" value="4" oninput="updatePeriodViz()">
  <span class="ctrl-val" id="vP">4</span>
  <span class="ans-label">N:</span>
  <select id="selN" class="answer-input" style="width:70px;" onchange="updatePeriodViz()">
    <option value="16">16</option><option value="32">32</option><option value="64">64</option>
  </select>
</div>
<div class="note-box"><strong>Multiple measurements:</strong> if gcd(P,&ell;)&gt;1 we get only a divisor of P. Take several measurements and compute P = lcm(all denominators). Example: N=312, P=24. M&#x2081;=195 &rarr; 5/8, M&#x2082;=208 &rarr; 2/3. lcm(8,3)=24=P &#x2713;</div>
<div class="ex-block">
  <div class="ex-header"><span class="ex-tag">Ex 7.1</span><span class="ex-title">Extract period</span></div>
  <div class="ex-body"><p>N=240, P=20 (unknown). Measurement gives M=120. Compute C=M/N. Is the denominator equal to P?</p></div>
  <div class="answer-area">
    <div class="answer-row">
      <span class="ans-label">C =</span><input class="answer-input" id="a71a" placeholder="fraction" style="width:80px;">
      <span class="ans-label">denom=</span><input class="answer-input" id="a71b" placeholder="int" style="width:60px;">
      <button class="btn sm" onclick="chk2('a71a','1/2','a71b','2','f71')">Check</button>
      <button class="hint-toggle" onclick="showHint('h71')">hint</button>
    </div>
    <div class="feedback hint" id="h71">C=120/240=1/2. Denominator=2, a divisor of P=20. Need another measurement to recover P=20.</div>
    <div class="feedback" id="f71"></div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- S8 Continued Fractions -->
<section class="section" id="s8">
<div class="section-num">Section 08</div>
<h2>Continued Fractions: When N mod P &ne; 0</h2>
<p>When N is not divisible by P, QFT peaks are only approximate. We get M and know M/N &asymp; &ell;/P. The continued fraction algorithm finds the exact fraction.</p>
<div class="def">
  <div class="def-title">Continued Fraction Algorithm</div>
  r&#x2080;/r&#x2081; = q&#x2080; + 1/(q&#x2081; + 1/(q&#x2082; + &hellip;)) &nbsp; where &nbsp; q&#x1D62; = &lfloor;r&#x1D62;/r&#x1D62;&#x208A;&#xB9;&rfloor;, r&#x1D62;&#x208A;&#xB9; = r&#x1D62;&#x208B;&#xB9; mod r&#x1D62;. Truncating early gives approximations whose denominators are candidates for P.
</div>
<h3>Worked example: N=256, P=10, M=77</h3>
<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">C = 77/256:</div><div class="mstep-body">&asymp; 0.30078 &nbsp; (true ratio &ell;/P = 3/10 = 0.3)</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Expand:</div><div class="mstep-body">77/256 = 0+1/(3+1/(3+2/25))</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Truncate (drop 2/25):</div><div class="mstep-body">77/256 &asymp; 1/(3+1/3) = <strong style="color:var(--green);">3/10</strong> &nbsp; denominator 10 = P &#x2713;</div></div>
</div>
<div style="border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:6px;padding:1rem;margin:1rem 0;background:#fdfcf8;">
  <div style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:0.6rem;">Interactive: Continued Fraction Calculator</div>
  <div class="controls" style="flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
    <span class="ans-label">M=</span><input id="cf_M" type="number" class="answer-input" value="77" style="width:70px;">
    <span class="ans-label">N=</span><input id="cf_N" type="number" class="answer-input" value="256" style="width:70px;">
    <button class="btn sm" onclick="computeCF()">Expand</button>
  </div>
  <div class="live" id="cfResult">Enter M and N, then click Expand.</div>
</div>
<div class="ex-block">
  <div class="ex-header"><span class="ex-tag">Ex 8.1</span><span class="ex-title">Continued fraction</span></div>
  <div class="ex-body"><p>N=100, M=33. Best rational approximation of 33/100 with denominator below 100?</p></div>
  <div class="answer-area">
    <div class="answer-row">
      <span class="ans-label">Best approx =</span>
      <input class="answer-input wide" id="a81" placeholder="e.g. 1/3">
      <button class="btn sm" onclick="chkFree('a81',['1/3','33/100'],'f81')">Check</button>
      <button class="hint-toggle" onclick="showHint('h81')">hint</button>
    </div>
    <div class="feedback hint" id="h81">33/100 = 0+1/(3+1/33) &asymp; 1/3. Denominator 3 is the P candidate.</div>
    <div class="feedback" id="f81"></div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- S9 Shor Full -->
<section class="section" id="s9">
<div class="section-num">Section 09</div>
<h2>Shor: Full Circuit and Complexity</h2>
<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Initial:</div><div class="mstep-body">|&psi;&#x2080;&#x27E9; = |0&#x27E9;&#x2E3E;log&#x2082;N &otimes; |0&#x27E9;&#x2E3E;log&#x2082;n</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">After H&#x2E3E;n:</div><div class="mstep-body">(1/&radic;N) &sum;&#x2096; |0&#x27E9;|k&#x27E9;</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">After U&#x1D453;:</div><div class="mstep-body">(1/&radic;N) &sum;&#x2096; |x&#x1D49; mod n&#x27E9;|k&#x27E9;</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Measure f(&ell;):</div><div class="mstep-body">Periodic state with period r</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Apply QFT&#x2099;:</div><div class="mstep-body">Peaks at multiples of N/P</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--green);">Measure M:</div><div class="mstep-body">Use continued fractions to find P = r. Done!</div></div>
</div>
<h3>n=15, x=7 example</h3>
<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Setup:</div><div class="mstep-body">N=1024, P=4, N/P=256</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">|&psi;&#x2081;&#x27E9;:</div><div class="mstep-body">(1/&radic;N)(|1&#x27E9;|0&#x27E9;+|7&#x27E9;|1&#x27E9;+|4&#x27E9;|2&#x27E9;+|13&#x27E9;|3&#x27E9;+|1&#x27E9;|4&#x27E9;+&hellip;)</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Measure |4&#x27E9;:</div><div class="mstep-body">Collapses to period-4 state (positions 2,6,10,&hellip;)</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">M=768:</div><div class="mstep-body">768/1024=3/4 &rarr; P=4. gcd(48,15)=3, gcd(50,15)=5 &#x2713;</div></div>
</div>
<h3>Complexity</h3>
<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">QFT gates:</div><div class="mstep-body">&asymp; b&sup2;</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">U&#x1D453; gates:</div><div class="mstep-body">&asymp; b&sup3; (modular exponentiation)</div></div>
  <hr class="math-sep">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--green);">Total:</div><div class="mstep-body" style="color:var(--green);font-weight:600;">O(b&sup3;) &mdash; polynomial! &nbsp; vs Classical O(b&middot;2&#x1D47;)</div></div>
</div>
<div class="ex-block">
  <div class="ex-header"><span class="ex-tag">Ex 9.1</span><span class="ex-title">Shor vs classical</span></div>
  <div class="ex-body"><p>For b=1024 bit RSA, estimate log&#x2081;&#x2030;(classical gates / Shor gates).</p></div>
  <div class="answer-area">
    <div class="answer-row">
      <span class="ans-label">log&#x2081;&#x2030;(ratio) &asymp;</span>
      <input class="answer-input" id="a91" placeholder="~300" style="width:100px;">
      <button class="btn sm" onclick="chkApprox('a91',300,50,'f91')">Check</button>
      <button class="hint-toggle" onclick="showHint('h91')">hint</button>
    </div>
    <div class="feedback hint" id="h91">Classical &asymp;2&#x2081;&#x2030;&#xB2;&#x2074;. Quantum &asymp;10&#x2079;. log&#x2081;&#x2030;(ratio) &asymp; 1024&middot;0.301 &minus; 9 &asymp; 300.</div>
    <div class="feedback" id="f91"></div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- PART III HEADER -->
<div style="background:var(--green);color:white;padding:0.45rem 1rem;margin:2rem 0 0;border-radius:var(--border-r);font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.68rem;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;">Part III &mdash; Grover&rsquo;s Algorithm</div>

<!-- S10 Grover Search -->
<section class="section" id="s10">
<div class="section-num">Section 10</div>
<h2>Grover&rsquo;s Algorithm: Quantum Search</h2>
<p>Grover&rsquo;s algorithm (1996) solves unstructured search with a quadratic quantum speedup. Given N items and one special target x*, classically you need N/2 checks on average. Grover does it in about &radic;N steps.</p>
<div class="def">
  <div class="def-title">The Search Problem</div>
  <strong>Given:</strong> f: &#x7B;0,&hellip;,N&minus;1&#x7D; &rarr; &#x7B;0,1&#x7D; with exactly one x* where f(x*)=1.<br>
  <strong>Find:</strong> x*. Classical: N/2 evaluations. Quantum: O(&radic;N).
</div>
<h3>The oracle U&#x1D453;</h3>
<div class="math-block">
  <div class="eq">U&#x1D453; |x&#x27E9; = (&minus;1)&#x1D453;&#x207A;&#x1D499;&#x207B; |x&#x27E9;</div>
  <div class="eq"><span class="eq-note">|x&#x27E9; &rarr; &minus;|x&#x27E9; if x=x* &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; |x&#x27E9; &rarr; +|x&#x27E9; if x&ne;x*</span></div>
</div>
<div class="note-box"><strong>U&#x1D453; is unitary:</strong> U&#x1D453;&dagger;U&#x1D453;|x&#x27E9; = (&minus;1)&#xB2;|x&#x27E9; = |x&#x27E9; &#x2713;</div>
<h3>Algorithm steps</h3>
<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--accent);">Step 1:</div><div class="mstep-body">H&#x2E3E;n|0&#x27E9;&#x2E3E;n &rarr; equal superposition |&psi;&#x2081;&#x27E9; = (1/&radic;N) &sum;&#x2096; |x&#x27E9;.</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--accent);">Step 2:</div><div class="mstep-body">Apply U&#x1D453;: flips amplitude of x* from +1/&radic;N to &minus;1/&radic;N.</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--accent);">Step 3:</div><div class="mstep-body">Apply diffusion U&#x1D48A; (next section): amplifies x*, suppresses others.</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--accent);">Repeat:</div><div class="mstep-body">Repeat Steps 2&ndash;3 &asymp; &radic;N times, then measure &rarr; x* with probability &asymp; 1.</div></div>
</div>
<canvas id="cvGrover" width="540" height="220"></canvas>
<div class="canvas-caption">Amplitude distribution. Step through to see the oracle flip and diffusion amplification in action.</div>
<div class="controls" style="gap:0.5rem;">
  <button class="btn sm" onclick="groverStep(0)">Initial |&psi;&#x2081;&#x27E9;</button>
  <button class="btn sm" onclick="groverStep(1)">After U&#x1D453;</button>
  <button class="btn sm" onclick="groverStep(2)">After U&#x1D48A;</button>
  <button class="btn sm" onclick="groverStep(3)">Round 2</button>
</div>
<div class="ex-block">
  <div class="ex-header"><span class="ex-tag">Ex 10.1</span><span class="ex-title">Oracle action</span></div>
  <div class="ex-body"><p>What does U&#x1D453; do to |x*&#x27E9; where f(x*)=1?</p></div>
  <div class="answer-area">
    <div class="answer-row">
      <span class="ans-label">U&#x1D453;|x*&#x27E9; =</span>
      <input class="answer-input wide" id="a101" placeholder="-|x*⟩">
      <button class="btn sm" onclick="chkFree('a101',['-|x*⟩','-|x*>','minus|x*>'],'f101')">Check</button>
      <button class="hint-toggle" onclick="showHint('h101')">hint</button>
    </div>
    <div class="feedback hint" id="h101">U&#x1D453;|x&#x27E9; = (&minus;1)&#x1D453;&#x207A;&#x1D499;&#x207B;|x&#x27E9;. For x=x*, f(x*)=1, so U&#x1D453;|x*&#x27E9; = &minus;|x*&#x27E9;.</div>
    <div class="feedback" id="f101"></div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- S11 Diffusion Operator -->
<section class="section" id="s11">
<div class="section-num">Section 11</div>
<h2>The Diffusion Operator: Inversion about the Mean</h2>
<p>After U&#x1D453; flips the phase of x*, the diffusion operator U&#x1D48A; converts this phase flip into an amplitude boost by reflecting every amplitude about the current mean &mu;.</p>
<div class="def">
  <div class="def-title">Diffusion Operator</div>
  <div class="math-block" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">
    <div class="eq">U&#x1D48A; = 2|s&#x27E9;&#x27E8;s| &minus; I &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; where &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; |s&#x27E9; = H&#x2E3E;n|0&#x27E9; = <span class="scalar">1/&radic;N</span> &sum;&#x2096; |x&#x27E9;</div>
  </div>
  Action on &sum;&#x2096; &alpha;&#x2096; |x&#x27E9;: each amplitude &alpha;&#x2096; &rarr; 2&mu; &minus; &alpha;&#x2096;, where &mu; = (1/N)&sum;&#x2096; &alpha;&#x2096; is the mean.
</div>
<h3>Why this amplifies x*</h3>
<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">Before U&#x1D453;:</div><div class="mstep-body">All &alpha;&#x2096; = 1/&radic;N. Mean &mu; = 1/&radic;N.</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">After U&#x1D453;:</div><div class="mstep-body">&alpha;&#x2096;* = &minus;1/&radic;N; &alpha;&#x2096; = +1/&radic;N for x&ne;x*. New mean &mu; &asymp; (N&minus;2)/(N&radic;N).</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">After U&#x1D48A;:</div><div class="mstep-body">x* amplitude: 2&mu; &minus; (&minus;1/&radic;N) &asymp; <strong style="color:var(--green);">3/&radic;N</strong> (tripled!)<br>Others: 2&mu; &minus; 1/&radic;N &asymp; 1/&radic;N (roughly unchanged, slightly decreased)</div></div>
</div>
<div class="insight"><strong>Geometric picture:</strong> Inversion about the mean is a reflection. x* sits below the mean (negative amplitude), so reflecting about the mean throws it upward by twice the distance. Each round amplifies x* by ~2/&radic;N.</div>
<h3>Precise calculation for one round</h3>
<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">After round r:</div><div class="mstep-body">Amplitude of x* &asymp; (2r+1)/&radic;N &nbsp;&rarr;&nbsp; P(x*) = (2r+1)&sup2;/N</div></div>
</div>
<div class="note-box"><strong>U&#x1D48A; is unitary:</strong> U&#x1D48A;&dagger;U&#x1D48A; = (2|s&#x27E9;&#x27E8;s|&minus;I)&sup2; = 4|s&#x27E9;&#x27E8;s|s&#x27E9;&#x27E8;s| &minus; 4|s&#x27E9;&#x27E8;s| + I = I &#x2713; (using &#x27E8;s|s&#x27E9;=1)</div>
<div class="ex-block">
  <div class="ex-header"><span class="ex-tag">Ex 11.1</span><span class="ex-title">Amplitude after one round, N=4</span></div>
  <div class="ex-body">
    <p>For N=4 after U&#x1D453;: &alpha;&#x2096;* = &minus;1/2, &alpha;&#x2096; = +1/2 for the other 3 states. Mean &mu; = (&minus;1/2+3&middot;1/2)/4 = 1/4. Compute x* amplitude after U&#x1D48A;.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="answer-area">
    <div class="answer-row">
      <span class="ans-label">&alpha;&#x2096;* after U&#x1D48A; =</span>
      <input class="answer-input" id="a111" placeholder="fraction" style="width:80px;">
      <button class="btn sm" onclick="chkFree('a111',['1','1.0','one'],'f111')">Check</button>
      <button class="hint-toggle" onclick="showHint('h111')">hint</button>
    </div>
    <div class="feedback hint" id="h111">2&mu; &minus; &alpha;&#x2096;* = 2&middot;(1/4) &minus; (&minus;1/2) = 1/2 + 1/2 = 1. P(x*) = 1&sup2; = 100%! Grover finds x* in ONE round for N=4.</div>
    <div class="feedback" id="f111"></div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- S12 Grover Rounds -->
<section class="section" id="s12">
<div class="section-num">Section 12</div>
<h2>Optimal Rounds and Summary</h2>
<h3>How many rounds?</h3>
<p>After r rounds the x* amplitude is &asymp;(2r+1)/&radic;N. For P(x*)&asymp;1 we need (2r+1)&sup2;&asymp;N, giving:</p>
<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--green);">Optimal rounds:</div><div class="mstep-body" style="color:var(--green);font-weight:600;">r &asymp; (&pi;/4)&radic;N</div></div>
</div>
<h3>Complete circuit</h3>
<div class="circuit">
  <div class="circuit-row">
    <span class="circuit-label">|0&#x27E9;&#x207F;</span>
    <div class="circuit-gate h" style="font-size:0.75rem;">H&#x2E3E;n</div>
    <div class="circuit-gate" style="border-color:var(--accent);color:var(--accent);">U&#x1D453;</div>
    <div class="circuit-gate" style="border-color:var(--orange);color:var(--orange);">U&#x1D48A;</div>
    <div class="circuit-gate" style="border-color:var(--accent);color:var(--accent);">U&#x1D453;</div>
    <div class="circuit-gate" style="border-color:var(--orange);color:var(--orange);">U&#x1D48A;</div>
    <span style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--muted);">&hellip;&times;&radic;N&hellip;</span>
    <div class="circuit-meas">M</div>
    <span class="circuit-out">x* w.p. &asymp; 1</span>
  </div>
</div>

<div style="border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:6px;padding:1rem;margin:1rem 0;background:#fdfcf8;">
  <div style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:0.6rem;">Interactive: Grover Probability Simulator</div>
  <div class="controls" style="flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
    <span class="ans-label">N=</span><input id="grv_N" type="number" class="answer-input" value="16" style="width:70px;">
    <span class="ans-label">x*=</span><input id="grv_xs" type="number" class="answer-input" value="3" style="width:70px;">
    <button class="btn sm" onclick="runGroverSim()">Start</button>
    <button class="btn sm" onclick="groverRound()">+ One round</button>
  </div>
  <canvas id="cvGroverSim" height="160"></canvas>
  <div class="live" id="groverSimInfo">Click Start to initialise.</div>
</div>

<h3>Algorithm summary</h3>
<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">U&#x1D453;|x&#x27E9;</div><div class="mstep-body">= (&minus;1)&#x1D453;&#x207A;&#x1D499;&#x207B; |x&#x27E9; &nbsp; (phase oracle)</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">U&#x1D48A;</div><div class="mstep-body">= 2|s&#x27E9;&#x27E8;s| &minus; I &nbsp; (diffusion = inversion about mean)</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label">|s&#x27E9;</div><div class="mstep-body">= (1/&radic;N) &sum;&#x2096; |x&#x27E9; = H&#x2E3E;n|0&#x27E9;</div></div>
  <div class="mstep"><div class="mstep-label" style="color:var(--green);">Speedup:</div><div class="mstep-body" style="color:var(--green);font-weight:600;">Classical N/2 &rarr; Quantum O(&radic;N) &mdash; quadratic speedup</div></div>
</div>

<div class="ex-block">
  <div class="ex-header"><span class="ex-tag">Ex 12.1</span><span class="ex-title">Grover rounds for N=64</span></div>
  <div class="ex-body"><p>Use r &asymp; (&pi;/4)&radic;N to compute the number of rounds for N=64.</p></div>
  <div class="answer-area">
    <div class="answer-row">
      <span class="ans-label">r &asymp;</span>
      <input class="answer-input" id="a121" placeholder="integer" style="width:60px;">
      <button class="btn sm" onclick="chkApprox('a121',6,1,'f121')">Check</button>
      <button class="hint-toggle" onclick="showHint('h121')">hint</button>
    </div>
    <div class="feedback hint" id="h121">r &asymp; (&pi;/4)&middot;8 &asymp; 6.28 &rarr; r &asymp; 6 rounds.</div>
    <div class="feedback" id="f121"></div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="ex-block">
  <div class="ex-header"><span class="ex-tag">Ex 12.2</span><span class="ex-title">Shor vs Grover speedup</span></div>
  <div class="ex-body"><p>Which provides a greater speedup: Shor or Grover?</p></div>
  <div class="answer-area">
    <div class="answer-row">
      <span class="ans-label">Answer:</span>
      <input class="answer-input wide" id="a122" placeholder="Shor or Grover?">
      <button class="btn sm" onclick="chkFree('a122',['shor','shor\'s'],'f122')">Check</button>
      <button class="hint-toggle" onclick="showHint('h122')">hint</button>
    </div>
    <div class="feedback hint" id="h122">Shor: exponential speedup O(b&sup3;) vs O(b&middot;2&#x1D47;). Grover: quadratic speedup O(&radic;N) vs O(N). Shor&rsquo;s advantage is vastly greater.</div>
    <div class="feedback" id="f122"></div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<script is:inline>
/* ── Utilities ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
function goTo(id){ var el=document.getElementById(id); if(el) el.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'}); }
function showHint(id){ document.getElementById(id).classList.toggle('show'); }
function setFb(id,ok,msg){ var el=document.getElementById(id); el.className='feedback show '+(ok?'ok':'no'); el.textContent=msg; }
function chkFree(iid,accepted,fbId){
  var v=document.getElementById(iid).value.trim().toLowerCase().replace(/[\s\u27e9>]/g,'');
  var ok=accepted.some(function(a){ return a.trim().toLowerCase().replace(/[\s\u27e9>]/g,'')===v; });
  document.getElementById(iid).className='answer-input '+(ok?'ok':'no');
  setFb(fbId,ok,ok?'\u2713 Correct!':'\u2717 Not quite \u2014 check the hint.');
}
function chk2(i1,e1,i2,e2,fb){
  var v1=document.getElementById(i1).value.trim(), v2=document.getElementById(i2).value.trim();
  var ok1=v1===e1, ok2=v2===e2;
  document.getElementById(i1).className='answer-input '+(ok1?'ok':'no');
  document.getElementById(i2).className='answer-input '+(ok2?'ok':'no');
  setFb(fb,ok1&&ok2,(ok1&&ok2)?'\u2713 Both correct!':'\u2717 Check each value.');
}
function chkApprox(iid,target,tol,fbId){
  var v=parseFloat(document.getElementById(iid).value.replace(',','.'));
  var ok=!isNaN(v)&&Math.abs(v-target)<=Math.max(tol,0.5);
  document.getElementById(iid).className='answer-input '+(ok?'ok':'no');
  setFb(fbId,ok,ok?('\u2713 Correct! \u2248 '+target):('\u2717 Expected \u2248 '+target));
}

/* ── QFT Drag-and-drop builder ─────────────────────────────── */
var qftDragging = null;
document.addEventListener('dragstart', function(e){
  var g=e.target.closest('.qb-gate'); if(g){ qftDragging=g.dataset.gate; e.dataTransfer.effectAllowed='copy'; }
});
function slotOver(e){ e.preventDefault(); e.currentTarget.classList.add('drag-over'); }
function slotLeave(e){ e.currentTarget.classList.remove('drag-over'); }
function slotDrop(e){
  e.preventDefault();
  e.currentTarget.classList.remove('drag-over');
  if(!qftDragging) return;
  placeGate(e.currentTarget, qftDragging);
  qftDragging=null;
}
function slotClick(slot){ if(slot.dataset.placed) removeGate(slot,null); }
var gLbls={'H':'H','O4':'\u03a9\u2084','O8':'\u03a9\u2088','SW':'\u21c4'};
function placeGate(slot,gate){
  slot.dataset.placed=gate;
  slot.className='qb-slot has-gate';
  slot.textContent=gLbls[gate]||gate;
  var x=document.createElement('span'); x.className='qb-slot-x'; x.innerHTML='\xd7';
  x.onclick=function(ev){ ev.stopPropagation(); removeGate(slot,ev); };
  slot.appendChild(x);
  updateQFTFormula();
}
function removeGate(slot,ev){
  if(ev) ev.stopPropagation();
  delete slot.dataset.placed;
  slot.className='qb-slot';
  slot.textContent='';
  var x=document.createElement('span'); x.className='qb-slot-x'; x.innerHTML='\xd7';
  x.onclick=function(ev2){ ev2.stopPropagation(); removeGate(slot,ev2); };
  slot.appendChild(x);
  updateQFTFormula();
}
function getGrid(){
  var g=[[],[]];
  for(var row=0;row<2;row++){
    var slots=document.querySelectorAll('[data-row="'+row+'"]');
    slots.forEach(function(s){ g[row].push(s.dataset.placed||null); });
  }
  return g;
}
var formulaSteps={
  '1-0-H':'Applied H to |k\u2081\u27e9:\n\n|\u03c8\u27e9 = \u00bd(|0\u27e9 + (-1)\u1d4c\xb9|1\u27e9) \u2297 |k\u2080\u27e9\n\nFirst qubit now in superposition.\nPhase (-1)\u1d4c\xb9 depends on k\u2081.',
  '1-1-O4':'Applied ctrl-\u03a9\u2084 (ctrl=k\u2080, tgt=k\u2081 wire):\n\n|\u03c8\u27e9 = \u00bd(|0\u27e9 + \u03c9\u2084\u1d4c\u2080(-1)\u1d4c\xb9|1\u27e9) \u2297 |k\u2080\u27e9\n\nAdded phase \u03c9\u2084 = j when k\u2080=1.\nSecond binary-fraction factor built!',
  '0-1-H':'Applied H to |k\u2080\u27e9:\n\n|\u03c8\u27e9 = \u00bd(|0\u27e9 + (-1)\u1d4c\u2080|1\u27e9) \u2297 (|0\u27e9 + \u03c9\u2084\u1d4c\u2080(-1)\u1d4c\xb9|1\u27e9)\n\nBoth factors complete!\nOutput in REVERSE order: q\u2081\u2297q\u2080.\nAdd SWAP to fix.',
  '0-2-SW':'Applied SWAP:\n\nFinal QFT\u2084 state (correct order):\n|\u03c8\u27e9 = \u00bd(|0\u27e9+(-1)\u1d4c\u2080|1\u27e9) \u2297 (|0\u27e9+\u03c9\u2084\u1d4c\u2080(-1)\u1d4c\xb9|1\u27e9)\n\n\u2713 Matches product formula!\n\u03a9\u2084 = S gate (\u03c9\u2084 = j)',
  '0-3-SW':'Applied SWAP (col 4):\n\n\u2713 QFT\u2084 complete with SWAP!',
};
function updateQFTFormula(){
  var g=getGrid(), el=document.getElementById('qftFormula'), chk=document.getElementById('qftCheck');
  var placed=[];
  for(var row=0;row<2;row++) for(var col=0;col<4;col++) if(g[row][col]) placed.push({row:row,col:col,gate:g[row][col]});
  if(!placed.length){
    el.innerHTML='|\u03c8\u27e9 = |k\u2081\u27e9 \u2297 |k\u2080\u27e9\n\nInitial state.\nDrag gates to build QFT\u2084.';
    chk.textContent=''; return;
  }
  var last=placed[placed.length-1];
  var key=last.row+'-'+last.col+'-'+last.gate;
  var desc=formulaSteps[key];
  if(desc) el.innerHTML=desc;
  else{
    var glist=placed.map(function(p){ return (gLbls[p.gate]||p.gate)+' r'+p.row; }).join(', ');
    el.innerHTML='Gates: '+glist+'\n\nKeep adding to complete QFT\u2084.';
  }
  var r0=g[0], r1=g[1];
  var ok=(r1[0]==='H'&&r1[1]==='O4'&&r0[1]==='H'&&(r0[2]==='SW'||r0[3]==='SW'));
  if(ok){ chk.textContent='\u2713 Correct QFT\u2084!'; chk.style.color='var(--green)'; }
  else{ chk.textContent=placed.length+' gate(s) placed'; chk.style.color='var(--muted)'; }
}
function loadQFT4Solution(){
  resetQFTBuilder();
  var delay=0;
  [['1','0','H'],['1','1','O4'],['0','1','H'],['0','2','SW']].forEach(function(spec){
    setTimeout(function(){ placeGate(document.querySelector('[data-row="'+spec[0]+'"][data-col="'+spec[1]+'"]'),spec[2]); }, delay+=350);
  });
}
function resetQFTBuilder(){
  document.querySelectorAll('.qb-slot').forEach(function(slot){
    delete slot.dataset.placed; slot.className='qb-slot'; slot.textContent='';
    var x=document.createElement('span'); x.className='qb-slot-x'; x.innerHTML='\xd7';
    x.onclick=function(ev){ ev.stopPropagation(); removeGate(slot,ev); };
    slot.appendChild(x);
  });
  updateQFTFormula();
  var c=document.getElementById('qftCheck'); if(c){ c.textContent=''; }
}

/* ── DFT Visualizer ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
var N_DFT=8, dftInput=[1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0];
function dft(x){
  var N=x.length,X=[];
  for(var q=0;q<N;q++){
    var re=0,im=0;
    for(var k=0;k<N;k++){ var a=2*Math.PI*k*q/N; re+=x[k]*Math.cos(a); im-=x[k]*Math.sin(a); }
    X.push(Math.sqrt(re*re+im*im)/Math.sqrt(N));
  }
  return X;
}
function setDFTPreset(name){
  if(name==='dirac'){ dftInput=[1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0]; }
  else if(name==='constant'){ dftInput=[1,1,1,1,1,1,1,1].map(function(v){ return v/Math.sqrt(8); }); }
  else if(name==='cos'){ dftInput=Array.from({length:8},function(_,k){ return Math.cos(2*Math.PI*k/8); }); }
  else { dftInput=Array.from({length:8},function(){ return Math.random()*2-1; }); }
  drawDFT();
}
function drawDFT(){
  var cv=document.getElementById('cvDFT'); if(!cv) return;
  cv.width=cv.parentElement.clientWidth-2;
  var ctx=cv.getContext('2d'),W=cv.width,H=cv.height;
  ctx.clearRect(0,0,W,H); ctx.fillStyle='#fafaf8'; ctx.fillRect(0,0,W,H);
  var X=dft(dftInput);
  var maxA=Math.max.apply(null,dftInput.map(Math.abs).concat(X).concat([0.001]));
  var bw=Math.min(28,(W-60)/(8*2)-3), cy=H/2;
  ctx.fillStyle='#2c5282'; ctx.font="9px 'IBM Plex Mono',monospace"; ctx.textAlign='center';
  ctx.fillText('Input x_k',W/4,12);
  for(var k=0;k<8;k++){
    var x=28+k*(bw+3), h=Math.abs(dftInput[k])/maxA*(H/2-20);
    ctx.fillStyle=dftInput[k]>=0?'#2c5282':'#c0392b';
    ctx.fillRect(x,dftInput[k]>=0?cy-h:cy,bw,h);
    ctx.fillStyle='#888'; ctx.font="8px 'IBM Plex Mono',monospace";
    ctx.fillText(k,x+bw/2,H-3);
  }
  ctx.fillStyle='#1a6b3a'; ctx.textAlign='center'; ctx.fillText('DFT |X_q|',3*W/4,12);
  var offX=W/2+10;
  for(var q=0;q<8;q++){
    var x2=offX+q*(bw+3), h2=X[q]/maxA*(H/2-20);
    ctx.fillStyle='#1a6b3a'; ctx.fillRect(x2,cy-h2,bw,h2);
    ctx.fillStyle='#888'; ctx.font="8px 'IBM Plex Mono',monospace"; ctx.textAlign='center';
    ctx.fillText(q,x2+bw/2,H-3);
  }
  ctx.strokeStyle='#ccc'; ctx.lineWidth=1;
  ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(10,cy); ctx.lineTo(W/2-5,cy); ctx.stroke();
  ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(W/2+5,cy); ctx.lineTo(W-10,cy); ctx.stroke();
}

/* ── Complexity canvas ──────────────────────────────────────── */
function drawComplexity(){
  var cv=document.getElementById('cvComplexity'); if(!cv) return;
  cv.width=cv.parentElement.clientWidth-2;
  var ctx=cv.getContext('2d'),W=cv.width,H=cv.height;
  ctx.clearRect(0,0,W,H); ctx.fillStyle='#fafaf8'; ctx.fillRect(0,0,W,H);
  var maxN=18;
  var px=function(n){ return 40+(n-1)/(maxN-1)*(W-60); };
  var maxY=maxN*Math.pow(2,maxN);
  var py=function(v){ return H-30-Math.min(v,maxY)/maxY*(H-50); };
  ctx.strokeStyle='#ede9dd'; ctx.lineWidth=0.8;
  [0.25,0.5,0.75,1].forEach(function(f){ var y=H-30-f*(H-50); ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(40,y); ctx.lineTo(W-10,y); ctx.stroke(); });
  ctx.strokeStyle='#c0392b'; ctx.lineWidth=2;
  ctx.beginPath();
  for(var n=1;n<=maxN;n++){ var y=py(n*Math.pow(2,n)); n===1?ctx.moveTo(px(n),y):ctx.lineTo(px(n),y); }
  ctx.stroke();
  ctx.fillStyle='#c0392b'; ctx.font="10px 'IBM Plex Mono',monospace"; ctx.textAlign='left';
  ctx.fillText('Classical FFT: O(n\xb72\u207f)',px(7)+5,py(7*Math.pow(2,7))-5);
  ctx.strokeStyle='#2c5282'; ctx.lineWidth=2; ctx.beginPath();
  for(var n2=1;n2<=maxN;n2++){ var y2=py(n2*n2); n2===1?ctx.moveTo(px(n2),y2):ctx.lineTo(px(n2),y2); }
  ctx.stroke();
  ctx.fillStyle='#2c5282'; ctx.fillText('QFT: O(n\xb2)',px(8),py(64)-10);
  ctx.strokeStyle='#888'; ctx.lineWidth=1; ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(40,H-30); ctx.lineTo(W-10,H-30); ctx.stroke();
  ctx.fillStyle='#888'; ctx.font="10px 'IBM Plex Mono',monospace"; ctx.textAlign='center'; ctx.fillText('n (qubits)',W/2,H-5);
}

/* ── Period visualizer ──────────────────────────────────────── */
function updatePeriodViz(){
  var P=parseInt(document.getElementById('slP').value);
  var N=parseInt(document.getElementById('selN').value);
  document.getElementById('vP').textContent=P;
  drawPeriod(P,N);
}
function drawPeriod(P,N){
  var cv=document.getElementById('cvPeriod'); if(!cv) return;
  cv.width=cv.parentElement.clientWidth-2;
  var ctx=cv.getContext('2d'),W=cv.width,H=cv.height;
  ctx.clearRect(0,0,W,H); ctx.fillStyle='#fafaf8'; ctx.fillRect(0,0,W,H);
  var bw=Math.max(2,(W-40)/N-1);
  ctx.fillStyle='#2c5282'; ctx.font="9px 'IBM Plex Mono',monospace"; ctx.textAlign='center';
  ctx.fillText('Periodic signal (P='+P+')',W/2,14);
  ctx.strokeStyle='#ccc'; ctx.lineWidth=1; ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(20,H/4+5); ctx.lineTo(W-10,H/4+5); ctx.stroke();
  for(var k=0;k<N;k++){
    var x=20+k*(bw+1); if(k%P===0){ ctx.fillStyle='#2c5282'; ctx.fillRect(x,H/4+5-(H/4-20),Math.max(1,bw),H/4-20); }
  }
  ctx.fillStyle='#1a6b3a'; ctx.textAlign='center'; ctx.fillText('QFT spectrum \u2014 peaks at multiples of N/P='+(N/P).toFixed(1),W/2,H/2+18);
  ctx.strokeStyle='#ccc'; ctx.lineWidth=1; ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(20,3*H/4+5); ctx.lineTo(W-10,3*H/4+5); ctx.stroke();
  for(var q=0;q<N;q++){
    var x2=20+q*(bw+1), re=0, im=0;
    for(var k2=0;k2<N;k2++) if(k2%P===0){ var ang=2*Math.PI*k2*q/N; re+=Math.cos(ang); im-=Math.sin(ang); }
    var amp=Math.sqrt(re*re+im*im)/Math.sqrt(N);
    var h=amp*(H/4-20)*3;
    ctx.fillStyle=amp>0.3?'#1a6b3a':'#a0c4b0';
    if(h>0) ctx.fillRect(x2,3*H/4+5-h,Math.max(1,bw),h);
  }
  var step=N/P;
  for(var i=0;i<P;i++){ var xp=20+Math.round(i*step)*(bw+1)+bw/2; ctx.fillStyle='#c0392b'; ctx.font="8px 'IBM Plex Mono',monospace"; ctx.textAlign='center'; ctx.fillText('\u2191',xp,3*H/4-8); }
}

/* ── Order finder ────────────────────────────────────────────── */
function gcd(a,b){ while(b){ var t=b; b=a%b; a=t; } return a; }
function computeOrder(){
  var n=parseInt(document.getElementById('shor_n').value);
  var x=parseInt(document.getElementById('shor_x').value);
  var el=document.getElementById('orderResult');
  if(isNaN(n)||isNaN(x)||x<2||x>=n){ el.textContent='Invalid input.'; return; }
  if(gcd(x,n)>1){ el.textContent='gcd('+x+','+n+')='+gcd(x,n)+' > 1 \u2014 lucky! Already a factor.'; return; }
  var pow=1;
  for(var r=1;r<=1000;r++){
    pow=(pow*x)%n;
    if(pow===1){
      var msg='Order r='+r+'\n'+x+'^'+r+' mod '+n+' = 1';
      if(r%2===0){
        var half=1; for(var i=0;i<r/2;i++) half=(half*x)%n;
        var f1=gcd(half-1,n), f2=gcd(half+1,n);
        if(f1>1&&f1<n) msg+='\nFactor: gcd('+x+'^('+r+'/2)-1, '+n+') = '+f1;
        if(f2>1&&f2<n) msg+='\nFactor: gcd('+x+'^('+r+'/2)+1, '+n+') = '+f2;
      }
      el.textContent=msg; return;
    }
  }
  el.textContent='Order not found in 1000 iterations.';
}

/* ── Continued fractions ─────────────────────────────────────── */
function computeCF(){
  var M=parseInt(document.getElementById('cf_M').value);
  var N=parseInt(document.getElementById('cf_N').value);
  var el=document.getElementById('cfResult');
  if(isNaN(M)||isNaN(N)||N===0){ el.textContent='Invalid input.'; return; }
  var r0=M,r1=N, steps=[], fracs=[], a=0,b=1,c=1,d=0;
  for(var i=0;i<20&&r1!==0;i++){
    var q=Math.floor(r0/r1); steps.push('q'+i+'='+q);
    var pn=q*c+a, qn=q*d+b; a=c; b=d; c=pn; d=qn;
    fracs.push(pn+'/'+qn);
    var tmp=r1; r1=r0%r1; r0=tmp; if(r1===0) break;
  }
  el.textContent='Expansion: ['+steps.join('; ')+']\nConvergents: '+fracs.join(' \u2192 ')+'\nCandidate P = '+d;
}

/* ── Grover amplitude stepper ────────────────────────────────── */
var GAMPS=[]; var GN=8; var GXS=2;
function groverStep(step){
  if(step===0){ GAMPS=new Array(GN).fill(1/Math.sqrt(GN)); }
  else if(step===1){ GAMPS=GAMPS.map(function(a,i){ return i===GXS?-a:a; }); }
  else if(step===2){ var mu=GAMPS.reduce(function(s,a){ return s+a; },0)/GN; GAMPS=GAMPS.map(function(a){ return 2*mu-a; }); }
  else {
    GAMPS=GAMPS.map(function(a,i){ return i===GXS?-a:a; });
    var mu2=GAMPS.reduce(function(s,a){ return s+a; },0)/GN; GAMPS=GAMPS.map(function(a){ return 2*mu2-a; });
  }
  drawGroverAmps();
}
function drawGroverAmps(){
  var cv=document.getElementById('cvGrover'); if(!cv) return;
  cv.width=cv.parentElement.clientWidth-2;
  var ctx=cv.getContext('2d'),W=cv.width,H=cv.height;
  ctx.clearRect(0,0,W,H); ctx.fillStyle='#fafaf8'; ctx.fillRect(0,0,W,H);
  var bw=Math.min(40,(W-60)/GN-4), cy=H/2;
  var maxA=Math.max.apply(null,GAMPS.map(Math.abs).concat([0.01]));
  ctx.strokeStyle='#ccc'; ctx.lineWidth=1; ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(20,cy); ctx.lineTo(W-10,cy); ctx.stroke();
  var mu=GAMPS.reduce(function(s,a){ return s+a; },0)/GN;
  var muY=cy-mu/maxA*(H/2-20);
  ctx.strokeStyle='#888'; ctx.lineWidth=1; ctx.setLineDash([3,3]);
  ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(20,muY); ctx.lineTo(W-10,muY); ctx.stroke();
  ctx.setLineDash([]);
  ctx.fillStyle='#888'; ctx.font="9px 'IBM Plex Mono',monospace"; ctx.textAlign='right';
  ctx.fillText('\u03bc='+mu.toFixed(3),W-12,muY-3);
  GAMPS.forEach(function(a,i){
    var x=25+i*(bw+4), h=a/maxA*(H/2-20);
    ctx.fillStyle=i===GXS?'#c0392b':'#2c5282';
    if(h>0) ctx.fillRect(x,cy-h,bw,h); else ctx.fillRect(x,cy,bw,-h);
    ctx.fillStyle='#888'; ctx.font="9px 'IBM Plex Mono',monospace"; ctx.textAlign='center';
    ctx.fillText(i===GXS?'x*':i,x+bw/2,H-3);
    ctx.fillStyle=i===GXS?'#c0392b':'#2c5282';
    var ly=h>0?cy-h-5:cy-h+13;
    ctx.fillText(a.toFixed(2),x+bw/2,ly);
  });
}

/* ── Grover simulator ────────────────────────────────────────── */
var simAmps=[],simN=16,simXs=3,simRound=0;
function runGroverSim(){
  simN=parseInt(document.getElementById('grv_N').value)||16;
  simXs=Math.min(parseInt(document.getElementById('grv_xs').value)||3, simN-1);
  simAmps=new Array(simN).fill(1/Math.sqrt(simN)); simRound=0;
  drawGroverSim();
}
function groverRound(){
  if(!simAmps.length){ runGroverSim(); return; }
  simAmps=simAmps.map(function(a,i){ return i===simXs?-a:a; });
  var mu=simAmps.reduce(function(s,a){ return s+a; },0)/simN;
  simAmps=simAmps.map(function(a){ return 2*mu-a; });
  simRound++;
  drawGroverSim();
}
function drawGroverSim(){
  var cv=document.getElementById('cvGroverSim'); if(!cv) return;
  cv.width=cv.parentElement.clientWidth-2;
  var ctx=cv.getContext('2d'),W=cv.width,H=cv.height;
  ctx.clearRect(0,0,W,H); ctx.fillStyle='#fafaf8'; ctx.fillRect(0,0,W,H);
  if(!simAmps.length){ ctx.fillStyle='#888'; ctx.font="12px 'IBM Plex Mono',monospace"; ctx.textAlign='center'; ctx.fillText('Click Start',W/2,H/2); return; }
  var bw=Math.max(2,(W-40)/simN-2), cy=H-25;
  var maxA=Math.max.apply(null,simAmps.map(Math.abs).concat([0.01]));
  var pxs=simAmps[simXs]*simAmps[simXs];
  ctx.strokeStyle='#ccc'; ctx.lineWidth=1; ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(20,cy); ctx.lineTo(W-10,cy); ctx.stroke();
  simAmps.forEach(function(a,i){
    var x=20+i*(bw+2), h=a/maxA*(H-50);
    ctx.fillStyle=i===simXs?'#c0392b':'#2c5282';
    ctx.fillRect(x,cy-(h>0?h:0),Math.max(1,bw),Math.abs(h));
    if(i===simXs){ ctx.fillStyle='#c0392b'; ctx.font="8px 'IBM Plex Mono',monospace"; ctx.textAlign='center'; ctx.fillText('x*',x+bw/2,H-3); }
  });
  var el=document.getElementById('groverSimInfo');
  if(el) el.textContent='Round '+simRound+' \u00b7 P(x*) = '+(pxs*100).toFixed(1)+'% \u00b7 Optimal rounds \u2248 '+Math.round(Math.PI/4*Math.sqrt(simN));
}

/* ── Init ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
window.addEventListener('load', function(){
  setTimeout(function(){ drawDFT(); drawComplexity(); updatePeriodViz(); groverStep(0); runGroverSim(); }, 400);
});
</script>
